.TH DSMIL-STATUS 1 "2025-10-11" "Dell MIL-SPEC Tools 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dsmil-status \- Query Dell MIL-SPEC DSMIL device status

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dsmil-status
.RI [ OPTIONS ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dsmil-status
queries and displays the current status of all 84 DSMIL devices on
Dell Latitude 5450 MIL-SPEC hardware. It provides information about
device availability, configuration, security status, and performance.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Display detailed device information
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-json
Output in JSON format for scripting
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-device =\fIDEVICE\fR
Query specific device (e.g., 0x8000)
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quarantine
Show only quarantined devices
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-color
Enable colored output (default: auto-detect)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message

.SH OUTPUT
Default output shows:
.IP \[bu] 2
Total device count (should be 84)
.IP \[bu]
Devices by group (6 groups)
.IP \[bu]
Quarantined devices (5 critical)
.IP \[bu]
Module status and version
.IP \[bu]
Performance metrics
.IP \[bu]
Thermal status

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Display all device status:
.RS
dsmil-status
.RE

.PP
Show detailed information:
.RS
dsmil-status --verbose
.RE

.PP
Query specific device:
.RS
dsmil-status --device 0x8000
.RE

.PP
JSON output for scripting:
.RS
dsmil-status --json | jq '.devices[] | select(.quarantined == true)'
.RE

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success - all devices operational
.TP
.B 1
Module not loaded or device unavailable
.TP
.B 2
Hardware error detected

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /dev/dsmil0
DSMIL device interface
.TP
.B /sys/devices/platform/dsmil/
Sysfs interface for device queries

